******
[2] Summaries
- Fri 5 Jul 2019. Case summary
[Le Figaro (trans., abridged, edited)]
http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/ebola-en-rdc-plus-de-1600-deces-une-nouvelle-zone-touchee-20190705


The 1600 death toll from the Ebola outbreak was crossed on Thursday [4 Jul 2019] in 2 eastern provinces of the Democratic Republic of Congo, where the virus caused a casualty in a new area bordering Uganda and Sudan South, said the Ministry of Health on Friday [45 Jul 2019]. "Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2382, of which 2288 are confirmed and 94 are probable. In total, there were 1606 deaths (1512 confirmed and 94 probable) and 666 people healed," reads the daily bulletin of the Ministry of Health dated Thursday [4 Jul 2019].

"A case has been reported in Ariwara, Ituri, since Monday [1 Jul 2019]. The people have even died," a spokesman for the Congolese Ministry of Health told AFP. The infected person, the mother of 5 infected children, 2 of whom died of Ebola, fled Beni (North Kivu) to neighboring Ituri to escape the epidemic response teams, health officials said in a bulletin dated Monday [1 Jul 2019].

"To date, 177 family contacts have been listed in Ariwara, and 40 contacts have already been vaccinated," according to health authorities. Ariwara is a locality in northern Ituri located about 10 km [6.2 mi] from Uganda, where a case from the DRC was reported in June [2019]. South Sudan is more than 60 km [37.3 mi] away.

--
